title: Data Analysis/Stats
content:
Descriptive(behaviors/changes overall or individual), Relational(how things happening are related), Causal(what factors cause what's happening)
Informational Model: Entity(objects), Location(spatial/conceptual), Event(occurrences/discovered facts)
Interpreting Data: Hypothesis, Conduct Study, Interpret Results
Normal Distribution - Central value with no left or right bias (68% of data within 1 std dev)
Standard Deviation - Typical measure in spread of data
F-Statistic - Yields probability (p-value) difference is due to chance
F = (between-group variability)/(within-group variability)
